## Part I

### 1. Dataset Construction

The dataset combines four monthly U.S. series from 1985M1 to 2023M3:

- **EPU**: News-Based Policy Uncertainty Index (levels), from policyuncertainty.com
- **PAYEMS**: Nonfarm payroll employment, seasonally adjusted — transformed to month-on-month growth rate: 100 × (X_t / X_{t-1} − 1)
- **INDPRO**: Industrial production index, seasonally adjusted — same transformation
- **PCEPI**: Personal consumption expenditures price index, seasonally adjusted — same transformation

After computing growth rates, the usable sample starts at 1985M2 (458 observations).

![Data Figure](output/data_figure.png)

**Figure note:** The four panels show the raw level series used to construct the dataset, covering 1985M1 to 2023M3. Top left: PCE price index (PCEPI), showing a steady upward trend with a slight acceleration post-2020. Top right: nonfarm payroll employment (PAYEMS, in thousands), showing long-run employment growth with clear contractions during the 2008–2009 financial crisis and the COVID-19 pandemic (2020). Bottom left: industrial production index (INDPRO), showing similar cyclical patterns. Bottom right: the News-Based Economic Policy Uncertainty index in levels, showing elevated volatility and a large spike during the COVID-19 pandemic. All series were downloaded from FRED (PAYEMS, INDPRO, PCEPI) and policyuncertainty.com (EPU), seasonally adjusted where applicable.

