## Part II

### 1. Unconditional Forecasts

Using the VAR estimated on 1985M2–2019M12, we produce unconditional forecasts for 12 months ahead starting from March 2023. Future reduced-form residuals are set to zero in expectation.

**Employment growth (PAYEMS):** The model predicts positive employment growth throughout the entire 12-month horizon. Growth starts at +0.043% in April 2023, remains flat in May, then increases gradually and monotonically, reaching +0.097% by March 2024. The forecast never turns negative, reflecting the VAR's mean-reversion toward the long-run positive average.

**Industrial production growth (INDPRO):** Industrial production growth starts slightly negative (−0.029% in April, −0.031% in May 2023), turns positive in July 2023 (+0.020%), and increases steadily thereafter, reaching +0.126% by March 2024. The brief initial contraction reflects the low level of INDPRO growth observed in March 2023 (+0.376% the prior month, but the model's dynamics pull toward a transitory dip before recovery).

